events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Orlando Magic

headlines.description: — Cole Anthony had 23 points, 10 rebounds and nine assists, Franz Wagner added 21 points and the Orlando Magic beat the San Antonio Spurs 133-113 on Friday night for their eighth victory in nine games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Magic beat Spurs 133-113 for 8th victory in 9 games

headlines.description: — Joel Embiid scored 44 points, James Harden had a career-high 21 assists in a triple-double and the Philadelphia 76ers overcame a 20-point first-half deficit to beat the Los Angeles Clippers 119-114 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Embiid, Harden help 76ers beat Clippers for homestand sweep

headlines.description: — Trae Young had 26 points and 13 assists, Dejounte Murray added 26 points, and the Atlanta Hawks used a dominant third quarter to beat the struggling Detroit Pistons 130-105 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Young, Murray power Hawks past Pistons, 130-105

headlines.description: — Jaylen Brown scored 23 of his 36 points in the fourth quarter to help the Boston Celtics pull away for a 121-109 victory over the Minnesota Timberwolves on Friday night that halted their season-worst three-game losing streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brown's 4th quarter carries Celtics past T-Wolves, 121-109

headlines.description: — Kevin Durant scored 24 points, and the Nets held Giannis Antetokounmpo scoreless in the fourth quarter to beat the Milwaukee Bucks 118-100 on Friday night, winning their eighth straight to match their longest winning streak since moving to Brooklyn...
headlines.shortLinkText: Nets beat Bucks, tie longest win streak in Brooklyn at 8

headlines.description: — Pascal Siakam had 26 points and nine assists, O.G. Anunoby scored 26 points and the Toronto Raptors rolled to a 118-107 victory over the Cavaliers on Friday night, becoming the first East team to win in Cleveland this season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Siakam and Anunoby score 26, Raptors beat Cavs 118-107

events.name: Chicago Bulls at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — DeMar DeRozan’s jumper with less than a second to play gave the Chicago Bulls a 118-117 victory over the New York Knicks on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: DeRozan's jumper gives Bulls 118-117 victory over Knicks

headlines.description: — Tyrese Haliburton hit a 3-pointer in the final seconds and finished with a career-high 43 points, helping the Indiana Pacers to a 111-108 win over the Miami Heat on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Haliburton hits winning 3, scores 43 as Pacers beat Heat

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic scored a season-high 50 points, including 17 in the fourth quarter, and the Dallas Mavericks held on to beat the Houston Rockets 112-106 on Friday night.

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Trey Murphy III scored 23 points and the New Orleans Pelicans overcame the absence of leading scorer Zion Williamson and a nine-point fourth-quarter deficit to beat the Oklahoma City Thunder 128-125 in overtime on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Murphy scores 23, Pelicans beat Thunder in OT without Zion

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Denver Nuggets

headlines.description: — Jamal Murray returned to the lineup with 25 points and a season-high 12 assists, Nikola Jokic had 29 points and 11 assists, and the Denver Nuggets beat the Portland Trail Blazers 120-107 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Murray, Jokic lead Nuggets to 120-107 win over Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Jaren Jackson Jr. had 24 points and 11 rebounds, Desmond Bane scored 17 points in his return and the Memphis Grizzlies took advantage of Phoenix star Devin Booker's absence to rout the Suns 125-100 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bane returns, Grizzlies rout Booker-less Suns 125-100

headlines.description: — Kyle Kuzma scored 32 points and the Washington Wizards beat the Sacramento Kings 125-111 on Friday night to end a six-game trip.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kyle Kuzma scores 32 points, Wizards beat Kings 125-111

events.name: Charlotte Hornets at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Gordon Hayward got the tiebreaking layup on a goaltending call against LeBron James with 6.3 seconds to play, and the Charlotte Hornets held off the Los Angeles Lakers 134-130 Friday night for only their second victory in 11 games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hornets overcome LeBron's comeback, hold off Lakers 134-130
